<table width="55%" border="2">
  <tr> 
    <td height="1351"><p><strong><font size="3" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a name="navigation"></a><font size="5">Navigation 
        Overview</font><br>
        </font><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#top"><font size="1">back 
        to top</font></a> </font></strong></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Navigating through the Karaoke 
        Monster is a simple process, most easily performed by using the buttons 
        that are at the top of the header at each page. This buttons are arranged 
        in a logical order, each one taking users further into the progression 
        of making a karaoke MP3. See figure 1:<br>
        <br>
        <strong><em>Figure 1: Header Buttons<br>
        <img src="Karaoke_help_images/nav_overview.gif" width="432" height="258"> 
        </em></strong></font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Also, these buttons correspond 
        to the buttons users see on the Karaoke Monster entrance screen. See figure 
        2 for a view of these buttons (and note that the same numbers in figure 
        1 correspond to the exact same button in figure 2)</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><em>Figure 2: Header 
        Buttons - Intro</em> <br>
        <img src="Karaoke_help_images/nav_overview2.gif" width="432" height="313"> 
        </strong></font></p>
      <p><strong><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">1. &quot;Manage Files&quot; 
        <br>
        </font></strong><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">This button 
        will take users to the File Management area, where you can upload MP3s, 
        along with adding the Artist and Song Name.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>2. &quot;Add Lyrics&quot;</strong></font><br>
        <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">This button will take users 
        to the Area where you can manually type, search for and paste, and browse 
        through song lyrics for all the MP3s already in the Karaoke Monster system.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>3. &quot;Sync Lyrics&quot;</strong></font><br>
        <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">This button will take users to 
        the area where you can synchronize saved lyrics to MP3s.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>4. &quot;Test Karaoke&quot;<br>
        </strong>This will take users to an area where you can visually watch 
        your finished karaoke song in action. Also, you can edit small glitches 
        in synchronization here.<br>
        </font><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><br>
        </font><strong><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">5. &quot;Real 
        Karaoke&quot;</font></strong><br>
        <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Although this button does not 
        currently function in the prototype model, in a beta version this button 
        will take users to the club-ready production version of the karaoke song, 
        with fully-integrated graphics and colorful synchronization. </font></p>
      </td>
