<table width="55%" border="2">
  <tr>
    <td><p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a name="uploading"></a><strong><font size="5">Uploading 
        MP3s</font></strong><br>
        <a href="#top"><font size="1">back to top</font></a> </font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Uploading MP3s to the Karaoke 
        Monster System is managed through the File Manager page. See figure 1 
        for a image on the File Manager page (note the circled button on the top, 
        it is the button that takes users to the File Manager Page)</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><em>Figure 1: File 
        Manager Page<br>
        <img src="Karaoke_help_images/file_manager.gif" width="432" height="188"> 
        </em></strong></font></p>
      <p><strong><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">1. &quot;Upload Your 
        MP3&quot;</font></strong><em><strong><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><br>
        </font></strong></em><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">By clicking 
        on the &quot;Browse&quot; button next to the &quot;Upload Your MP3&quot; 
        input field, a traditional Windows file browsing window opens, allowing 
        users to navigate and select the proper MP3. Since the prototype model 
        currently only sorts MP3 by their file name, it is probably best to upload 
        MP3s with easy-to-remember names (example: name it &quot;Metallica_Unforgiven.mp3&quot; 
        instead of &quot;02-Live-Metallica-Unforgiven.mp3&quot;)</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>2. &quot;Artist&quot; 
        and &quot;Song Name&quot; <br>
        </strong>Once a MP3 is selected, users can input the proper Artist and 
        Song Name credits. This will allow for easy location of song lyrics on 
        the &quot;Add Lyrics&quot; page.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>3. &quot;Upload&quot;<br>
        </strong>Clicking the upload button will upload the selected MP3 to the 
        server. After one, or several, MP3s have been loaded, click on the &quot;Add 
        Lyrics&quot; button on the top of the page to go on to the second step 
        of karaoke producing.</font></p>
      </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="55%" border="2">
  <tr> 
    <td><p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a name="playing"></a><strong><font size="5">Playing 
        MP3s</font></strong><br>
        <a href="#top"><font size="1">back to top</font></a> </font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Playing MP3s that are on the 
        server is conducted on the &quot;Add Lyrics&quot; page. See figure 1 for 
        an image of the &quot;Add Lyrics&quot; page, note the highlighted area 
        that focuses on the MP3 player.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><em>Figure 1: MP3 Player<br>
        <img src="Karaoke_help_images/mp3_playergif.gif" width="432" height="366"> 
        </em></strong></font></p>
      <p><strong><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">1. Player Controls</font></strong><em><strong><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><br>
        </font></strong></em><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The Karaoke 
        Monster has the basic MP3 player controls (last track, stop, play, and 
        next track).</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>2. Uploaded Song Navigation<br>
        </strong>This menu allows users to view and select a particular MP3 to 
        play. Currently, the Karaoke Monster prototype only supports sorting the 
        MP3 by the file name.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">If any lyrics have been added 
        to songs, they will be viewable in the right window pane when a song is 
        selected in the MP3 player.</font></p>
      </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="55%" border="2">
  <tr> 
    <td><p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a name="searching"></a><strong><font size="5">Searching 
        for Lyrics</font></strong><br>
        <a href="#top"><font size="1">back to top</font></a> </font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Searching for lyrics for songs 
        is conducted on the &quot;Add Lyrics&quot; page. See figure 1.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><em>Figure 1: Searching 
        for Lyrics Menu</em></strong></font><br>
        <img src="Karaoke_help_images/lyric_search.gif" width="432" height="389"> 
      </p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>1. Searching for Lyrics 
        Text Box</strong><br>
        If a song was uploaded with a named Artist and Song Name fields filled, 
        the &quot;Search for Lyrics&quot; textbox will be automatically filled. 
        Otherwise, users can also manually type in search fields.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>2. &quot;Search&quot;</strong><br>
        Lyrics can be searched for through 3 different web services: Sing365.com, 
        Astraweb.com, and AZLyrics.com. When any of the three boxes are clicked, 
        a new window will open up, directing the user immediately to any available 
        matching song lyrics. These lyrics can then be copied (control+c on keyboard) 
        and pasted (control+v on keyboard) into the Song Lyric Window.</font></p>
      </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="55%" border="2">
  <tr> 
    <td><p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a name="adding"></a><strong><font size="5">Adding/ 
        Saving Lyrics</font></strong><br>
        <a href="#top"><font size="1">back to top</font></a> </font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Lyrics can either be hand-typed 
        into the Song Lyrics window in the &quot;Add Lyrics&quot; page, or can 
        be copied and pasted in using the &quot;Search for Lyrics&quot; Menu (see 
        Searching for Lyrics in this help file). Once lyrics are complete, the 
        save button can be clicked to archive the lyrics. See Figure 1.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Figure 1: Adding/ Saving 
        Lyrics<br>
        <img src="Karaoke_help_images/add_lyrics.gif" width="432" height="352"> 
        <br>
        </strong></font></p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="55%" border="2">
  <tr> 
    <td><p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a name="synchronizing"></a><strong><font size="5">Synchronizing 
        Lyrics to the MP3</font></strong><br>
        <a href="#top"><font size="1">back to top</font></a> </font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">To synch lyrics, a MP3 must 
        be loaded to the system and the proper lyrics must be saved to the system 
        (see &quot;Uploading MP3s&quot; and &quot;Adding/Saving Lyrics&quot; in 
        this help file). If this is done, then users can go to the &quot;Sync 
        Lyrics&quot; page of Karaoke Monster. There, a three-step process must 
        be followed to sync the lyrics. See Figure 1 for an image showing the 
        3-step progression:</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><em>Figure 1: 3-Step 
        Sync</em><br>
        <img src="Karaoke_help_images/synch_lyrics.gif" width="612" height="361"></strong></font></p>
      <p><strong><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">1. Starting the Sync<br>
        </font></strong><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">A user must 
        select the appropriate MP3, wait for the lyrics to load on the right hand 
        of the screen, and click play.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>2. Sync the Text to 
        the Song</strong></font><br>
        <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Once the song begins playing, 
        the user must now click the &quot;Sync Words&quot; button (has two musical 
        notes on it) or click alt+s on the keyboard for each word as it is 
        sung aloud. In other words, as a word is sung in the song, the user must 
        make a single click at that exact moment to synchronize the text lyrics 
        to the actual song. In the Lyrics window, the word currently selected 
        is highlighted, and each click of he mouse (or strike of alt + s) will 
        make the next successive word become highlighted. That way, users can 
        follow along to be sure that the proper word is being clicked on as the 
        song plays. Looking at the figure, the word &quot;yourself&quot; is currently 
        being highlighted, and a single click of the mouse will make the word 
        &quot;to&quot; highlighted, and so on, and so on, until the song is completed.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>3. Save the Sync</strong><br>
        Once complete, the user must simply click on the &quot;Save Sync&quot; 
        icon to archive the sync.</font></p>
      </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="55%" border="2">
  <tr> 
    <td height="632"><p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a name="karaoke"></a><font size="5"><strong>Playing 
        the Karaoke Songs</strong></font><br>
        <a href="#top"><font size="1">back to top</font></a> </font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Playing karaoke songs is done 
        in the &quot;Test Karaoke&quot; window of Karaoke Monster. See Figure 
        1.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><em>Figure 1: Playing 
        the Karaoke</em></strong><br>
        <img src="Karaoke_help_images/test_karaoke.gif" width="540" height="365"></font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>1. Select and Play 
        the Song</strong><br>
        In the left pane, users select the song they wish to karaoke and click 
        &quot;Play.&quot;</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>2. Sync of Text to 
        Song</strong><br>
        On the right pane, the words of the song will be highlighted as they are 
        sung in the song, thus creating a perfect custom karaoke.</font></p>
      </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="55%" border="2">
  <tr> 
    <td><p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a name="chnaging"></a><strong><font size="5">Changing/ 
        Editing the Karaoke Synch</font></strong><br>
        <a href="#top"><font size="1">back to top</font></a> </font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Since synchronizing the song 
        to the lyrics is a manual process, there is the possibility for user error. 
        While the user can simply redo the entire sync and resave it in the &quot;sync 
        Lyrics&quot; window, there is another advanced function that allows user 
        the option of manually tweaking karaoke efforts - the Advanced Duration 
        Edit. See figure 1 and the following steps for details.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><em><strong>Figure 1: Advanced 
        Duration Edit <br>
        <img src="Karaoke_help_images/advanced_sync.gif" width="540" height="282"></strong></em></font></p>
      <p><strong><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">1. Select the ADE Option 
        <br>
        </font></strong><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">In the &quot;Test 
        Karaoke&quot; window, a user may select the &quot;Advanced Duration Edit&quot; 
        checkbox to tweak, word-by-word, the karaoke sync.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>2. Changing the Milliseconds<br>
        </strong>Textboxes appear next to each word. These textboxes contain the 
        milliseconds that the karaoke highlighter &quot;sits&quot; on that given 
        word. If a word is skipped over too fast, the value can be increased, 
        or vice versa. It is important to note that changing the value of one 
        word will change when all subsequent words are highlighted. This may be 
        positive or negative, contingent upon the type of sync error that initially 
        occurred.</font></p>
      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>3. Saving Changes</strong><br>
        By clicking on this button, the new millisecond values are saved and archived 
        into Karaoke Monster.</font></p>
      </td>
  </tr>
</table>
